' ============================================================
' SIE SYSTEMIC PROCESS MANAGEMENT
'
' Two complementary packages:
' 1. Systemic Emergence Management - Creates/modifies SystemicPrimitives
' 2. Systemic Constraint Management - Ensures coherence of constraints
'
' Relationship: Constraint Management may trigger Emergence when
' resolution requires new primitives. Both are feedback-driven.
' ============================================================

frame "PD - SIE Systemic Process Management - v1" {

  note as ProcessOverview
    **Systemic Process Management Overview:**

    These processes implement SIE's self-governance capabilities,
    enabling automatic and human-assisted system definition evolution.

    **Systemics Theory Alignment:**
    - **Emergence** (Bertalanffy, Holland): EmergenceProcess creates new
      primitives—NOVELTY generation.
    - **Homeostasis** (Cannon, Ashby): CoherenceCheckProcess + ResolutionProcess
      maintain definition stability—EQUILIBRIUM maintenance.
    - **Requisite Variety** (Ashby): FeasibilityAssessment validates that
      mechanism variety ≥ constraint variety.

    **Emergence + Homeostasis = Adaptive System Definition**
    - Emergence proposes (variety expansion)
    - Homeostasis disposes (coherence validation, stabilization)
    - Together: "Order at the edge of chaos" (Kauffman)

    **SystemicPrimitive Integration:**
    All process classes are **SystemicPrimitives** as defined in sie-csdm-v1.puml.
    This enables cross-domain reasoning about processes themselves.

    **Relationship between packages:**
    - Emergence Management: Creates all primitives (NOVELTY)
    - Constraint Management: Ensures coherence (HOMEOSTASIS)
    - Constraint Management USES Emergence when resolution requires
      creation of new primitives.

    **Feedback topology (Homeostatic Loops):**
    - Vertical: Operator → Supervisor → Governor (intra-system)
    - Horizontal: Governor ↔ Governor (inter-system coherence)
    - Recursive: Constraints about constraints (meta-governance)

    **Human-in-the-loop modes (configurable per feature):**
    - Advisory: Propose actions, human decides
    - Semi-autonomous: Act within boundaries, escalate exceptions
    - Fully autonomous: Self-healing within approved policies
  end note

  ' ============================================================
  ' SYSTEMIC EMERGENCE MANAGEMENT PACKAGE
  ' ============================================================

  package "Systemic Emergence Management" as EmergencePackage {

    note as EmergenceNote
      **Purpose:**
      Creates and modifies SystemicPrimitives based on:
      - Observations (use cases, risks, incidents, operational signals)
      - Coherence feedback (from Constraint Management)
      - User requests (direct definition actions)
      - LLM proposals (AI-suggested primitives)

      **Scope:** ALL primitive types, not just constraints.
      - Structural: Components, Interfaces, Channels
      - Behavioral: Mechanisms, BehavioralRules, Effectors, Receptors
      - Governance: Policies, Governors, Supervisors
      - Constitutive: Purposes, Capacities, Functions, Modalities

      **Four-Plane Context:**
      - Observations come from Description Plane (sensed from State Plane)
      - Primitives are created in Definition Plane (CSDM)
      - Regulation Plane actuators enforce primitives on State Plane
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' EMERGENCE PROCESS
    ' ============================================================

    class EmergenceProcess {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getStatus(): ProcessStatus
      +getTrigger(): EmergenceTrigger
      +getObservations(): Observation[]
      +getProposedPrimitives(): ProposedPrimitive[]
      +getConfidenceScore(): Decimal
      +getApprovalStatus(): ApprovalStatus
      +getApprovedBy(): User
      +getCreatedAt(): DateTime
      +getCompletedAt(): DateTime
    }

    note top of EmergenceProcess
      EmergenceProcess is a SystemicPrimitive.
      It is part of CSDM's extensible process model.
      See sie-csdm-v1.puml SystemicPrimitive for base semantics.
    end note

    enum ProcessStatus {
      INITIATED
      ANALYZING
      PROPOSING
      AWAITING_APPROVAL
      APPROVED
      EXECUTING
      COMPLETED
      FAILED
      CANCELLED
    }

    class EmergenceTrigger {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getType(): TriggerType
      +getSource(): TriggerSource
      +getPayload(): Object
      +getTimestamp(): DateTime
      +getPriority(): Priority
    }

    enum TriggerType {
      OBSERVATION_RECEIVED
      COHERENCE_FEEDBACK
      USER_REQUEST
      LLM_PROPOSAL
      SCHEDULED_ANALYSIS
      THRESHOLD_BREACH
      EXTERNAL_CHANGE
    }

    enum TriggerSource {
      USER
      LLM
      COHERENCE_PROCESS
      FEEDBACK_LOOP
      SCHEDULER
      EXTERNAL_SYSTEM
    }

    enum Priority {
      LOW
      MEDIUM
      HIGH
      CRITICAL
    }

    ' ============================================================
    ' OBSERVATION HANDLING (Description Layer)
    ' ============================================================

    class Observation {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getSourceUri(): String
      +getSourceSystem(): String
      +getObservationType(): ObservationType
      +getCollectedAt(): DateTime
      +getLlmSummary(): String
      +getExtractedIntent(): Object
      +getConfidence(): Decimal
      +getRelatedPrimitives(): UUID[]
    }

    enum ObservationType {
      USE_CASE
      RISK_ANALYSIS
      INCIDENT_REPORT
      AUDIT_FINDING
      PERFORMANCE_METRIC
      DEPENDENCY_CHANGE
      REGULATORY_UPDATE
      ARCHITECTURE_DECISION
      USER_FEEDBACK
      OPERATIONAL_LOG
    }

    note top of Observation
      **Description Plane Primitive**

      Observations are sensed data from the State Plane,
      stored as REFERENCES (URIs) with cached LLM interpretation.
      Full content remains in source systems.

      LLM interprets observations to extract:
      - Intent: What the observation implies for system definition
      - Affected primitives: Which existing primitives relate
      - Confidence: How certain the interpretation is

      **Four-Plane Model:**
      - Definition Plane (CSDM): What SHOULD be
      - Description Plane (Observations): What IS KNOWN
      - Regulation Plane (Actuators): What ACTS to align
      - State Plane (External): What IS
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' PROPOSED PRIMITIVES
    ' ============================================================

    class ProposedPrimitive {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getPrimitiveType(): String
      +getOperation(): PrimitiveOperation
      +getProposedValues(): Object
      +getRationale(): String
      +getObservations(): Observation[]
      +getConfidence(): Decimal
      +getImpactAssessment(): ImpactAssessment
      +getStatus(): ProposalStatus
    }

    enum PrimitiveOperation {
      CREATE
      DEPRECATE
    }

    enum ProposalStatus {
      PROPOSED
      UNDER_REVIEW
      APPROVED
      REJECTED
      EXECUTED
    }

    class ImpactAssessment {
      +getAffectedPrimitives(): UUID[]
      +getCoherenceRisks(): String[]
      +getBreakingChanges(): Boolean
      +getEstimatedEffort(): String
    }

    note top of ProposedPrimitive
      Primitives are IMMUTABLE once created.
      "Modification" = DEPRECATE old + CREATE new.
      This preserves full audit trail and enables rollback.
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' EMERGENCE STRATEGIES
    ' ============================================================

    abstract class EmergenceStrategy {
      +getName(): String
      +getApplicableTriggerTypes(): TriggerType[]
      +getTargetPrimitiveTypes(): String[]
      +analyze(trigger, evidence): ProposedPrimitive[]
    }

    class ConstraintEmergenceStrategy {
      +getPolicyTypes(): PolicyType[]
    }
    EmergenceStrategy <|-- ConstraintEmergenceStrategy

    class StructuralEmergenceStrategy {
      +getComponentTypes(): String[]
    }
    EmergenceStrategy <|-- StructuralEmergenceStrategy

    class BehavioralEmergenceStrategy {
      +getMechanismTypes(): String[]
    }
    EmergenceStrategy <|-- BehavioralEmergenceStrategy

    note top of EmergenceStrategy
      Strategies encapsulate domain-specific emergence logic.

      Each strategy:
      - Analyzes observations for its domain
      - Proposes primitives with rationale
      - Assesses impact on existing definitions

      Strategies use LLM for:
      - Observation interpretation
      - Primitive synthesis
      - Rationale generation
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' EMERGENCE RELATIONSHIPS
    ' ============================================================

    EmergenceProcess "1" *--> "1" EmergenceTrigger : triggeredBy
    EmergenceProcess "1" *--> "0..*" Observation : uses
    EmergenceProcess "1" *--> "0..*" ProposedPrimitive : proposes
    EmergenceProcess "1" o--> "0..1" EmergenceStrategy : usesStrategy
    ProposedPrimitive "1" *--> "1" ImpactAssessment : has
    ProposedPrimitive "1" o--> "0..*" Observation : justifiedBy
  }

  ' ============================================================
  ' SYSTEMIC CONSTRAINT MANAGEMENT PACKAGE
  ' ============================================================

  package "Systemic Constraint Management" as ConstraintPackage {

    note as ConstraintNote
      **Purpose:**
      Ensures coherence of Policies and BehavioralRules through:
      - Incoherence detection (conflicts, orphans, cycles, drift)
      - Resolution proposal (create, deprecate, adjust scope)
      - Lifecycle management (proposal → publication → integration)
      - Feedback processing (integration success/failure)

      **Triggers Emergence when:**
      - Resolution requires new constraint
      - Resolution requires new structural primitive
      - Detected gap requires policy/rule creation
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' COHERENCE CHECK PROCESS
    ' ============================================================

    class CoherenceCheckProcess {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getStatus(): ProcessStatus
      +getTrigger(): CoherenceTrigger
      +getScope(): CoherenceScope
      +getDetectedIncoherences(): Incoherence[]
      +getStartedAt(): DateTime
      +getCompletedAt(): DateTime
    }

    class CoherenceTrigger {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getType(): CoherenceTriggerType
      +getAffectedPrimitives(): UUID[]
      +getTimestamp(): DateTime
    }

    enum CoherenceTriggerType {
      ON_DEMAND
      ON_CHANGE
      SCHEDULED
      THRESHOLD
      PRE_PUBLISH
      INTEGRATION_FEEDBACK
    }

    class CoherenceScope {
      +getSystems(): UUID[]
      +getConstraintTypes(): ConstraintType[]
      +getIncoherenceTypes(): IncoherenceType[]
      +getDepth(): ScopeDepth
    }

    enum ConstraintType {
      FUNCTIONAL_POLICY
      VIABILITY_POLICY
      STRUCTURAL_POLICY
      BEHAVIORAL_RULE
    }

    enum ScopeDepth {
      SINGLE_CONSTRAINT
      SYSTEM_CONSTRAINTS
      CROSS_SYSTEM
      GLOBAL
    }

    ' ============================================================
    ' INCOHERENCE DETECTION
    ' ============================================================

    class Incoherence {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getType(): IncoherenceType
      +getSeverity(): Severity
      +getInvolvedPrimitives(): UUID[]
      +getDescription(): String
      +getDetectionMethod(): DetectionMethod
      +getDetectedAt(): DateTime
      +getResolutionStatus(): ResolutionStatus
    }

    enum IncoherenceType {
      LOGICAL_CONTRADICTION
      SCOPE_CONFLICT
      ORPHANED_CONSTRAINT
      CIRCULAR_DEPENDENCY
      STALE_REFERENCE
      SEMANTIC_DRIFT
      SCOPE_OVERLAP
      MISSING_OPERATIONALIZATION
      PRIORITY_CONFLICT
      TEMPORAL_CONFLICT
    }

    enum Severity {
      INFO
      WARNING
      ERROR
      CRITICAL
    }

    enum DetectionMethod {
      GRAPH_ANALYSIS
      FORMAL_VERIFICATION
      LLM_SEMANTIC_ANALYSIS
      PATTERN_MATCHING
      MANUAL_REVIEW
    }

    enum ResolutionStatus {
      UNRESOLVED
      RESOLUTION_PROPOSED
      RESOLUTION_APPROVED
      RESOLUTION_EXECUTING
      RESOLVED
      ACCEPTED_RISK
    }

    note top of IncoherenceType
      **Incoherence Types:**

      - LOGICAL_CONTRADICTION: Mutually exclusive conditions
      - SCOPE_CONFLICT: Multiple constraints claim same scope
      - ORPHANED_CONSTRAINT: Policy without operationalizing rule
      - CIRCULAR_DEPENDENCY: A → B → C → A
      - STALE_REFERENCE: References deleted primitive
      - SEMANTIC_DRIFT: Intent no longer matches reality
      - SCOPE_OVERLAP: Ambiguous authority boundaries
      - MISSING_OPERATIONALIZATION: Policy not translated to rules
      - PRIORITY_CONFLICT: Conflicting priorities
      - TEMPORAL_CONFLICT: Timing/sequencing conflicts
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' RESOLUTION PROCESS
    ' ============================================================

    class ResolutionProcess {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getStatus(): ProcessStatus
      +getIncoherence(): Incoherence
      +getProposedResolutions(): ProposedResolution[]
      +getSelectedResolution(): ProposedResolution
      +getApprovalStatus(): ApprovalStatus
      +getApprovedBy(): User
      +getEmergenceProcess(): EmergenceProcess
    }

    class ProposedResolution {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getStrategy(): ResolutionStrategy
      +getActions(): ResolutionAction[]
      +getRationale(): String
      +getConfidence(): Decimal
      +getImpactAssessment(): ImpactAssessment
      +getProposedBy(): ProposalSource
    }

    enum ResolutionStrategy {
      CREATE_CONSTRAINT
      DEPRECATE_CONSTRAINT
      ADJUST_SCOPE
      ADJUST_PRIORITY
      MERGE_CONSTRAINTS
      SPLIT_CONSTRAINT
      ADD_EXCEPTION
      ACCEPT_RISK
      ESCALATE
    }

    class ResolutionAction {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getType(): ActionType
      +getTargetPrimitive(): UUID
      +getChanges(): Object
      +getOrder(): Integer
    }

    enum ActionType {
      CREATE_PRIMITIVE
      UPDATE_STATUS
      DEPRECATE_PRIMITIVE
      LINK_PRIMITIVES
      UNLINK_PRIMITIVES
      TRIGGER_EMERGENCE
    }

    enum ProposalSource {
      LLM
      USER
      AUTOMATED_RULE
      PATTERN_MATCH
    }

    enum ApprovalStatus {
      PENDING
      APPROVED
      REJECTED
      AUTO_APPROVED
    }

    ' ============================================================
    ' INTEGRATION FEEDBACK
    ' ============================================================

    class IntegrationFeedback {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getConstraintId(): UUID
      +getConstraintType(): ConstraintType
      +getMechanismId(): UUID
      +getMechanismType(): MechanismType
      +getOutcome(): IntegrationOutcome
      +getFailureReason(): String
      +getIncoherenceDetails(): Incoherence
      +getTimestamp(): DateTime
    }

    enum MechanismType {
      GOVERNOR
      SUPERVISOR
      OPERATOR
    }

    enum IntegrationOutcome {
      SUCCESS
      FAILURE
      PARTIAL
    }

    note top of IntegrationFeedback
      Captures feedback when mechanisms attempt to integrate
      constraints (Policies, BehavioralRules).

      **Flow:**
      1. Governor publishes Policy
      2. Supervisor OPERATIONALIZES Policy → feedback
      3. Operator REALIZES BehavioralRule → feedback
      4. Feedback triggers coherence check if failure

      **Terminology:**
      - Governor OWNS Policy
      - Supervisor OPERATIONALIZES Policy → BehavioralRule
      - Supervisor OWNS BehavioralRule
      - Operator REALIZES BehavioralRule (is defined by it)

      This closes the feedback loop from execution back to
      definition, enabling self-correction.
    end note

    ' ============================================================
    ' FEASIBILITY ASSESSMENT (Pre-Integration)
    ' ============================================================

    class FeasibilityAssessment {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getConstraintId(): UUID
      +getConstraintType(): ConstraintType
      +getAssessorMechanism(): UUID
      +getAssessorType(): AssessorType
      +getOutcome(): FeasibilityOutcome
      +getRationale(): String
      +getBlockingIssues(): BlockingIssue[]
      +getProposedAdjustments(): ProposedAdjustment[]
      +getAssessedAt(): DateTime
    }

    enum AssessorType {
      SUPERVISOR
      OPERATOR
    }

    enum FeasibilityOutcome {
      FEASIBLE
      NOT_FEASIBLE
      FEASIBLE_WITH_ADJUSTMENTS
    }

    class BlockingIssue {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getDescription(): String
      +getIssueType(): BlockingIssueType
      +getAffectedCapabilities(): String[]
      +getSuggestedMitigation(): String
    }

    enum BlockingIssueType {
      MISSING_CAPABILITY
      RESOURCE_CONSTRAINT
      DEPENDENCY_UNAVAILABLE
      CONFLICTING_CONFIGURATION
      SCOPE_TOO_BROAD
      THRESHOLD_UNACHIEVABLE
      TEMPORAL_IMPOSSIBILITY
    }

    class ProposedAdjustment {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getAdjustmentType(): AdjustmentType
      +getTargetAttribute(): String
      +getCurrentValue(): Object
      +getProposedValue(): Object
      +getJustification(): String
    }

    enum AdjustmentType {
      NARROW_SCOPE
      RELAX_THRESHOLD
      ADD_EXCEPTION
      ADD_DEPENDENCY
      EXTEND_TIMELINE
      REDUCE_COVERAGE
    }

    note top of FeasibilityAssessment
      **Pre-Integration Viability Check**

      Occurs BEFORE publication (between APPROVED and PUBLISHED).

      **Purpose:**
      Answers "CAN this constraint be applied/realized?"
      Not "will it succeed?" but "is it technically feasible?"

      **Role mapping & Governance Hierarchy:**

      Governor OWNS Policy
         │
         ▼ Supervisor OPERATIONALIZES Policy
      Supervisor OWNS BehavioralRule
         │
         ▼ Operator REALIZES BehavioralRule
      Operator IS DEFINED BY BehavioralRule

      **Feasibility semantics:**
      - **Policy → Supervisor** assesses:
        "Can I OPERATIONALIZE this Policy into BehavioralRules?"
      - **BehavioralRule → Operator** assesses:
        "Can I EXIST to realize this BehavioralRule?"

      **Existential note for Operator:**
      An Operator doesn't just "implement" a BehavioralRule—
      it IS DEFINED BY it. Without the rule, the Operator has
      no essence, no behavior, no existence. This is existential
      feasibility, not merely functional feasibility.

      **Requisite Variety Validation (Ashby):**
      Feasibility Assessment is a VARIETY VALIDATOR:
      "Does the mechanism have enough variety to realize this constraint?"

      | Outcome | Variety Interpretation |
      |---------|------------------------|
      | FEASIBLE | Mechanism variety ≥ constraint variety |
      | NOT_FEASIBLE + MISSING_CAPABILITY | Variety deficit detected |
      | WITH_ADJUSTMENTS + ADD_DEPENDENCY | Proposes variety expansion |
      | WITH_ADJUSTMENTS + NARROW_SCOPE | Reduces constraint to match variety |

      **Workflow:**
      1. Constraint reaches APPROVED state
      2. System identifies relevant assessor(s)
      3. Each assessor provides FeasibilityAssessment
      4. If ALL feasible → proceed to PUBLISHED
      5. If ANY not feasible → go to NOT_FEASIBLE or
         FEASIBLE_WITH_ADJUSTMENTS states
      6. Author may accept adjustments or revise

      **Systemic semantics:**
      This implements ANTICIPATORY feedback (predict before act)
      vs. post-hoc IntegrationFeedback (observe after act).
    end note

    FeasibilityAssessment "1" *--> "0..*" BlockingIssue : reports
    FeasibilityAssessment "1" *--> "0..*" ProposedAdjustment : suggests

    ' ============================================================
    ' CONSTRAINT MANAGEMENT RELATIONSHIPS
    ' ============================================================

    CoherenceCheckProcess "1" *--> "1" CoherenceTrigger : triggeredBy
    CoherenceCheckProcess "1" *--> "1" CoherenceScope : scopes
    CoherenceCheckProcess "1" *--> "0..*" Incoherence : detects

    ResolutionProcess "1" o--> "1" Incoherence : resolves
    ResolutionProcess "1" *--> "1..*" ProposedResolution : proposes
    ResolutionProcess "1" o--> "0..1" ProposedResolution : selected
    ResolutionProcess "1" o--> "0..1" EmergenceProcess : triggers

    ProposedResolution "1" *--> "1..*" ResolutionAction : contains
    ProposedResolution "1" *--> "1" ImpactAssessment : has

    IntegrationFeedback "1" o--> "0..1" Incoherence : reveals
  }

  ' ============================================================
  ' CROSS-PACKAGE RELATIONSHIPS
  ' ============================================================

  ' Constraint Management triggers Emergence for new primitives
  ResolutionProcess "0..*" o--> "0..1" EmergenceProcess : triggersEmergence

  ' Emergence may receive feedback about constraint coherence
  EmergenceProcess "0..*" o--> "0..*" Incoherence : informedBy

  ' ============================================================
  ' CONFIGURATION MODEL
  ' ============================================================

  package "Process Configuration" as ConfigPackage {

    class ProcessConfiguration {
      +getId(): UUID
      +getName(): String
      +getApplicableProcesses(): String[]
      +getAutomationMode(): AutomationMode
      +getApprovalConfig(): ApprovalConfiguration
      +getTriggerConfig(): TriggerConfiguration
    }

    enum AutomationMode {
      ADVISORY
      SEMI_AUTONOMOUS
      FULLY_AUTONOMOUS
    }

    class ApprovalConfiguration {
      +getRequiredApprovers(): User[]
      +getMinApprovals(): Integer
      +getAutoApproveConditions(): String
      +getEscalationTimeout(): Duration
      +getEscalationTarget(): User
    }

    class TriggerConfiguration {
      +getEnabledTriggers(): TriggerType[]
      +getSchedule(): String
      +getThresholds(): Map<String, Number>
      +getCooldownPeriod(): Duration
    }

    class ConfigurationScope {
      +getScopeType(): ConfigScopeType
      +getScopeId(): UUID
    }

    enum ConfigScopeType {
      GLOBAL
      PER_SYSTEM
      PER_PRIMITIVE_TYPE
      PER_CONSTRAINT_TYPE
      PER_SEVERITY
    }

    note top of ProcessConfiguration
      Configuration is hierarchical and overridable:

      GLOBAL (default)
        └─ PER_SYSTEM
            └─ PER_PRIMITIVE_TYPE
                └─ PER_CONSTRAINT_TYPE
                    └─ PER_SEVERITY

      More specific scopes override less specific ones.

      Example configurations:
      - "Production systems: all proposals need manual approval"
      - "FunctionalPolicy: semi-autonomous creation"
      - "CRITICAL severity: always escalate to architect"
      - "ViabilityPolicy: require security team approval"
    end note

    ProcessConfiguration "1" *--> "1" ConfigurationScope : appliesTo
    ProcessConfiguration "1" *--> "1" ApprovalConfiguration : approvalRules
    ProcessConfiguration "1" *--> "1" TriggerConfiguration : triggerRules
  }

  ' ============================================================
  ' INTEGRATION ARCHITECTURE
  ' ============================================================

  note as IntegrationNote
    **Integration Architecture (Three-Layer Model):**

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │               DEFINITION LAYER (CSDM - PostgreSQL)          │
    │  What SHOULD be: Systems, Policies, Rules, Structure        │
    │  Source of truth for all SystemicPrimitives                 │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              ↑↓
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │               DESCRIPTION LAYER (Observations)              │
    │  What IS KNOWN: Sensed data with LLM interpretation         │
    │  Storage: Document DB (URI-referenced, decoupled)           │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              ↑↓
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │               STATE LAYER (External Systems)                │
    │  What IS: Actual runtime state                              │
    │  Sources: Logs, metrics, configs, CMDB, observability       │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

    **Processing Stack:**

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │                    LLM Orchestration Layer                  │
    │  • Observation interpretation (unstructured → intent)       │
    │  • Primitive proposal synthesis                             │
    │  • Semantic conflict detection                              │
    │  • Resolution suggestion with rationale                     │
    │  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │
    │  Technology: LangChain / Semantic Kernel / custom           │
    │  Models: GPT-4, Claude, or fine-tuned domain model          │
    └─────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │              SIE Process Engine (Core)                      │
    │  • Process orchestration (Emergence, Coherence)             │
    │  • State management (PostgreSQL)                            │
    │  • CSDSL validation & compilation                           │
    │  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │
    │  Technology: Custom (Kotlin/Java/Go)                        │
    └─────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │              Graph Analysis Layer (Neo4j)                   │
    │  • Dependency traversal                                     │
    │  • Cycle detection                                          │
    │  • Impact analysis                                          │
    │  • Causal chain exploration                                 │
    │  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │
    │  Sync: CDC from PostgreSQL                                  │
    └─────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │              Event Bus (Kafka)                              │
    │  • Process triggers                                         │
    │  • Integration feedback                                     │
    │  • Cross-process communication                              │
    │  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │
    │  Topics: emergence.*, coherence.*, feedback.*               │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │         Optional: CEL/OPA Runtime Evaluation                │
    │  • Fast constraint evaluation against actual state          │
    │  • Compiled from CSDSL expressions                          │
    │  • Used for runtime conformance checking                    │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
  end note
}

@enduml
